tudents to be honest and sincere in all their ways. Polite behaviour and gentleness in speech and manner will be insisted upon at all times.</li>\r\n	<li>Parents should supply their children with a wholesome &amp; substantial lunch each day, so that they will not be compelled to patronize dispensers of unwholesome food, outside the school.</li>\r\n	<li>No tiffin will be accepted for any students during the school hours, for security reasons.</li>\r\n	<li>Pupils must attend games and other activities outside school hours when required to do so and participation in such circumstances will be deemed necessary by the school authorities.</li>\r\n	<li>No student (except those in classes XI &amp; XII) is allowed to bring any 2-wheeler to school.</li>\r\n	<li>No 4-wheeler is allowed in school.</li>\r\n</ul>','School Rules and Regulations','','publish','open','open','','school-rules-and-regulations','','','2013-06-26 09:53:18','2013-06-26 09:53:18','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=192',0,'page','',0),(193,1,'2013-06-18 07:42:23','2013-06-18 07:42:23','','SCHOOL RULES AND REGULATIONS','','inherit','open','open','','192-revision','','','2013-06-18 07:42:23','2013-06-18 07:42:23','',192,'http://localhost/wordpress/192-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(194,1,'2013-06-21 06:15:49','2013-06-21 06:15:49','<ul>\n	<li>All the students are expected to come to school in full uniform, clean and neatly dressed. No relaxation, whatsoever, in uniform will be allowed.</li>\n	<li>Students should be in school at least five minutes before the first bell at 7.45 a.m. in summer and 8.15 a.m. in winter. Punctuality is very necessary.</li>\n	<li>Students will not be allowed to leave the school premises during the school hours without the Principal’s / Vice Principal’s permission.</li>\n	<li>No leave of absence will be granted except on prior written application from parents/guardians. Leave of absence will be granted only in exceptional circumstances. What the exceptional circumstances are, 