n','',0),(195,1,'2013-06-18 07:43:01','2013-06-18 07:43:01','<ul>\r\n	<li>All the students are expected to come to school in full uniform, clean and neatly dressed. No relaxation, whatsoever, in uniform will be allowed.\r\nStudents should be in school at least five minutes before the first bell at 7.45 a.m. in summer and 8.15 a.m. in winter. Punctuality is very necessary.\r\nStudents will not be allowed to leave the school premises during the school hours without the Principal’s / Vice Principal’s permission.\r\nNo leave of absence will be granted except on prior written application from parents/guardians. Leave of absence will be granted only in exceptional circumstances. What the exceptional circumstances are, will be determined by the school authorities. Defaulters will be fined.\r\nNo story books, comics, periodicals, pictures or newspapers except those allowed by the school shall be brought to the school nor circulated without the permission of the Principal/ Vice- Principal.\r\nNo jewellery is allowed in the school. Girls with pierced ears may wear thin silver wire earrings. Watches may be worn only by students of classes VII and above.\r\nNo borrowing or lending of money or exchanging of articles is allowed in the school.\r\nStudents will be required to make good any damages done to the school property.\r\nMobile phones are not allowed in the school. No student is allowed to bring any other electrical/electronic gadget to the school.\r\nStudents will be allowed to use the school telephone only in urgent cases and that too with the Principal\'s/Vice Principal’s permission. Visitors are not allowed to meet the students in school.\r\nThe school expects the students to be honest and sincere in all their ways. Polite behaviour and gentleness in speech and manner will be insisted upon at all times.\r\nParents should supply their children with a wholesome &amp; substantial lunch each day, so that they will not be compelled to patronize dispensers of unwholesome food, outside the school.\r\nNo tiffin will be accepted for any students during the school hours, for security reasons.\r\nPupils must attend games and other activities outside school hours when required to do so and participation in such circumstances will be deemed necessary by the school authorities.\r\nNo student (except those in classes XI &amp; XII) is allowed to bring any 2-wheeler to school.\r\nNo 4-wheeler is allowed in school</li>\r\n</ul>','SCHOOL RULES AND REGULATIONS','','inherit','open','open','','192-revision-2','','','2013-06-18 07:43:01','2013-06-18 07:43:01','',192,'http://localhost/wordpress/192-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(196,1,'2013-06-18 06:57:08','2013-06-18 06:57:08','<h1>Guidelines &amp; Rules</h1>\r\nExcellent Hostel facility is available for students of classes I to XII, where students are provided with cozy comforts of a home away from home, with all modern amenities. (only 40 seats).\r\n<h2>Rules</h2>\r\nThe school follow fue rules and are listed here\r\n<h2>School Timings</h2>\r\n<h5>SUMMER</h5>\r\nNursery 8.30 a.m. to 12.00 noon\r\nK.G 7.45 a.m. to 12.00 noon\r\nI to X 7.45 a.m. to 1.40 p.m.\r\nXI 7.45 a.m. to 12.00 p.m.\r\nXII 7.45 a.m. to 12.00 p.m.\r\n<h4>WINTER</h4>\r\nNursery 9.00 a.m. to 12.30 p.m.\r\nK.G 8.15 a.m. to 12.30 p.m.\r\nI to X 8.15 a.m. to 2.10 p.m.\r\nXI 8.15 a.m. to 12.30 p.m.\r\nXII 8.15 a.m. to 12.30 p.m.\r\n\r\nSATURDAY (CLASSES III ONWARDS)\r\n7.45 a.m. to 12.10 p.m. Summer\r\n8.15 a.m. to 12.40 p.m. Winter\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #800000;\">Note: The school gate closes at 7.45 a.m. (Summer) &amp; 8.15 a.m. (Winter)</span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #800000;\"> Late comers will be punished/action will be taken. Three late arrivals in a term would lead to the student being sent back home.</span>\r\n<h2>School Uniform</h2>\r\n<h5>Summer</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dark brown terrycot tunic/shorts/trousers (Classes VI onwards)</li>\r\n	<li>Light mustard terrycot blouse/shirt.</li>\r\n	<li>Black closed shoes/Black plain 