calhost/wordpress/?p=266',0,'revision','',0),(267,1,'2013-06-19 10:04:04','2013-06-19 10:04:04','[slideshow]','Facilities','','inherit','open','open','','74-revision-8','','','2013-06-19 10:04:04','2013-06-19 10:04:04','',74,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=267',0,'revision','',0),(268,1,'2013-06-19 10:04:25','2013-06-19 10:04:25','[gallery id=\"248\"]','Facilities','','inherit','open','open','','74-revision-9','','','2013-06-19 10:04:25','2013-06-19 10:04:25','',74,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=268',0,'revision','',0),(269,1,'2013-06-19 10:23:11','2013-06-19 10:23:11','[slideshow post_id=\"248\"]','Facilities','','inherit','open','open','','74-revision-10','','','2013-06-19 10:23:11','2013-06-19 10:23:11','',74,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=269',0,'revision','',0),(270,1,'2013-06-18 07:33:17','2013-06-18 07:33:17','<h4>About Mount Carmel School</h4>\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"left\" />\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Mount Carmel School is a Senior Secondary School being run under the aegis of Mount Carmel Educational Society, Chandigarh (Regd.), a group of Christian teachers, dedicated to the cause of complete moral, intellectual and social development of boys and girls. We derive our inspiration from the Lord Jesus Christ who loves children and we fully believe in the commandment given by Him, \'Love thy neighbour as thyself\'. On this, the motto of our school ‘Amor Vincit Omnia\' is based.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/founders.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-105\" alt=\"founders\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/founders-161x300.jpg\" width=\"161\" height=\"300\" /></a>Mount Carmel School was founded by Dr. Earnest Charles J. Samuel &amp; Dr. Annie Charles Samuel in April 1987.\r\n</strong></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">At present it has a strength of around 2200 students on rolls, in classes Pre-Nursery to XII. The school is Recognized by the Department of Education U.T., Chandigarh and is Affiliated to the Central Board of Secondary Education (C.B.S.E.), Delhi.</p>\r\nThe school has well qualified, experienced and dedicated teachers and boasts of excellent results in the All India Secondary School Examination conducted by the C.B.S.E. Besides laying emphasis on Academic Excellence, the students are encouraged to participate in various co-curricular &amp; extra-curricular activities in the field of performing Arts, Martial arts, FIne arts, Theatre etc.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/information\" target=\"_blank\"><div class=\"div_link\"><b>Comprehensive Information</b></div><a></center>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nVarious competitions and contests viz., Quiz, Recitation, Story telling, Calligraphy, Reading, Debate/Declamation, Dumb Charades, Essay/Short story writing, Drawing, Painting &amp; Singing etc., are held regularly, which help in the all round development of the students.\r\n\r\nThe school also lays emphasis on sports and games for the physical development of boys and girls. At present, the school extends Facilities for Basketball, Football, Cricket, Lawn Tennis, Net Ball, , Carrom, Chess, Kho-Kho, Karate, Gymnastics, Roller Skating, Sepak Takraw, Athletics etc. Computer education is imparted to students from class II onwards.\r\n\r\nThe school is situated in serene surroundings in a plot of around 3 acres, in sector 47 B, Chandigarh, the city beautiful situated at the foothills of the Shivalik Mountains a part of the Himalayas.\r\n\r\nExcellent Hostel facility is available for students of classes I to XII, where students are provided with cozy comforts of a home away from home, with all modern amenities. (only 40 seats). For further details, contact school reception from 8.00 am to 4.00 pm on any working day. Tel: 0172-2630145 , 6532783\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-25','','','2013-06-18 07:33:17','2013-06-18 07:33:17','',21,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=270',0,'revision','',0),(271,1,'2013-06-21 05:49:20','2013-06-21 05:49:20','<h4>About Mount Carmel School</h4>\r\n\r\n<hr align=\"left\" />\r\n<p align=\"justify\">Mount Carmel School is a Senior Secondary School being run under the aegis of Mount Carmel Educational Society, Chandigarh (Regd.), a group of Christian teachers, dedicated to the cause of complete moral, intellectual and social development of boys and girls. We derive our inspiration from the Lord Jesus Christ who loves children and we fully believe in the commandment given by Him, \'Love thy neighbour as thyself\'. On this, the motto of our school ‘Amor Vincit Omnia\' is based.</p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\"><strong><a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/founders.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-105\" alt=\"founders\" src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/founders-161x300.jpg\" width=\"161\" height=\"300\" /></a>Mount Carmel School was founded by Dr. Earnest Charles J. Samuel &amp; Dr. Annie Charles Samuel in April 1987.\r\n</strong></p>\r\n<p align=\"justify\">At present it has a strength of around 2200 students on rolls, in classes Pre-Nursery to XII. The school is Recognized by the Department of Education U.T., Chandigarh and is Affiliated to the Central Board of Secondary Education (C.B.S.E.), Delhi.</p>\r\nThe school has well qualified, experienced and dedicated teachers and boasts of excellent results in the All India Secondary School Examination conducted by the C.B.S.E. Besides laying emphasis on Academic Excellence, the students are encouraged to participate in various co-curricular &amp; extra-curricular activities in the field of performing Arts, Martial arts, FIne arts, Theatre etc.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=115\" target=\"_blank\"><div class=\"div_link\"><b>Comprehensive Information</b></div><a></center>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nVarious competitions and contests viz., Quiz, Recitation, Story telling, Calligraphy, Reading, Debate/Declamation, Dumb Charades, Essay/Short story writing, Drawing, Painting &amp; Singing etc., are held regularly, which help in the all round development of the students.\r\n\r\nThe school also lays emphasis on sports and games for the physical development of boys and girls. At present, the school extends Facilities for Basketball, Football, Cricket, Lawn Tennis, Net Ball, , Carrom, Chess, Kho-Kho, Karate, Gymnastics, Roller Skating, Sepak Takraw, Athletics etc. Computer education is imparted to students from class II onwards.\r\n\r\nThe school is situated in serene surroundings in a plot of around 3 acres, in sector 47 B, Chandigarh, the city beautiful situated at the foothills of the Shivalik Mountains a part of the Himalayas.\r\n\r\nExcellent Hostel facility is available for students of classes I to XII, where students are provided with cozy comforts of a home away from home, with all modern amenities. (only 40 seats). For further details, contact school reception from 8.00 am to 4.00 pm on any working day. Tel: 0172-2630145 , 6532783\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-26','','','2013-06-21 05:49:20','2013-06-21 05:49:20','',21,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=271',0,'revision','',0),(272,1,'2013-06-18 07:45:01','2013-06-18 07:45:01','<ul>\r\n	<li>All the students are expected to come to school in full uniform, clean and neatly dressed. No relaxation, whatsoever, in uniform will be allowed.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nStudents should be in school at least five minutes before the first bell at 7.45 a.m. in summer and 8.15 a.m. in winter. Punctuality is very necessary.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nStudents will not be allowed to leave the school premises during the school hours without the Principal’s / Vice Principal’s permission.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nNo leave of absence will be granted except on prior written application from parents/guardians. Leave of absence will be granted only in exceptional circumstances. What the exceptional circumstances are, will be determined by the school authorities. Defaulters will be fined.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nNo story books, comics, periodicals, pictures or newspapers except those allowed by the school shall be brought to the school nor circulated without the permission of the Principal/ Vice- Principal.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nNo jewellery is allowed in the school. Girls with pierced ears may wear thin silver wire earrings. Watches may be worn only by students of classes VII and above.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nNo borrowing or lending of money or exchanging of articles is allowed in the school.\r\nStudents will be required to make good any damages done to the school property.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nMobile phones are not allowed in the school. No student is allowed to bring any other electrical/electronic gadget to the school.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nStudents will be allowed to use the school telephone only in urgent cases and that too with the Principal\'s/Vice Principal’s permission. Visitors are not allowed to meet the students in school.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nThe school expects the students to be honest and sincere in all their ways. Polite behaviour and gentleness in speech and manner will be insisted upon at all times.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nParents should supply their children with a wholesome &amp; substantial lunch each day, so that they will not be compelled to patronize dispensers of unwholesome food, outside the school.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nNo tiffin will be accepted for any students during the school hours, for security reasons.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nPupils must attend games and other activities outside school hours when required to do so and participation in such circumstances will be deemed necessary by the school authorities.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nNo student (except those in classes XI &amp; XII) is allowed to bring any 2-wheeler to school.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\nNo 4-wheeler is allowed in school.</li>\r\n</ul>','SCHOOL RULES AND REGULATIONS','','inherit','open','open','','192-revision-3','','','2013-06-18 07:45:01','2013-06-18 07:45:01','',192,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=272',0,'revision','',0),(273,1,'2013-06-21 08:39:04','2013-06-21 08:39:04','<span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">I send my daughter to Mount Carmel School because of the safe environment and educational possibilities that this school offers. The teachers and staff alike are well aware of the troubles that parents nowadays have in making a decision where to send their children to school. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">Every year I am sending my daughter to this school I feel more confident than ever and she will have a better opportunity to learn all of the required skills to better prepare her for the technological world that lies ahead. Teachers communicate with the children and parents regarding any concerns with education and are more than willing to help the children with tutoring and keep the parents aware of any progress made.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">I hope to continue on this journey of education with my daughter, and to send her to Mount Carmel School school in the future possibly to earn some type of scholarship that would make her teachers very proud, along with her mother and father..</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #800000;\"><b> A<span style=\"font-family: Verdana;\">vni Srivastava</span></b></span>','Testimonials','','publish','open','open','','testimonials','','','2013-06-21 08:39:04','2013-06-21 08:39:04','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=273',0,'page','',0),(274,1,'2013-06-21 08:38:35','2013-06-21 08:38:35','','Testimonials','','inherit','open','open','','273-revision','','','2013-06-21 08:38:35','2013-06-21 08:38:35','',273,'http://localhost/wordpress/?p=274',0,'revision','',0),(275,1,'2013-06-18 07:23:03','2013-06-18 07:23:03','<h4>Contact Us</h4>\r\n<span style=\"color: #003366;\">Mount Carmel School</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #003366;\">Sector 47, Chandigarh</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=